  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Given KKK arrays of length NNN where the elements are bounded in the range [L,R][L, R][L,R].\n\nThe **Function value** of an array is defined as the sum of all elements present in it.\n\nIn one move you can change at most 111 element from all the arrays and the changed value must lie within the range [L,R][L, R][L,R].\n\nWhat is the minimum number of operations required to make the function value of all arrays equal?\n\n###Input\n\n\nThe first line of the input contains a single integer TTT denoting the number of test cases. The description of TTT test cases follows.\nThe first line of each test case contains four space-separated integers KKK, NNN, LLL, RRR.\nNext KKK lines contains an array of length NNN.",
    "constraints": [
      "1≤T≤51 \\leq T \\leq 51≤T≤5",
      "1≤K≤1051 \\leq K \\leq 10^51≤K≤105",
      "1≤N≤1051 \\leq N \\leq 10^51≤N≤105",
      "1≤N∗K≤1051 \\leq N*K \\leq 10^51≤N∗K≤105",
      "1≤L≤R≤1091 \\leq L \\leq R \\leq 10^91≤L≤R≤109",
      "Example Input`1",
      "4 3 1 9",
      "1 1 2",
      "1 2 3",
      "1 2 4",
      "1 2 2",
      "`Example Output`1",
      "`Explanation",
      "Change array 111 to [1,3,2][1, 3, 2][1,3,2]",
      "No change in array 222",
      "Change array 333 to [1,2,3][1, 2, 3][1,2,3]",
      "Change array 444 to [1,2,3][1, 2, 3][1,2,3]",
      "Sum of all arrays is equal."
    ],
